Now, we load the dataset and convert the data type of some columns to the expected values and replace some others to make it more meaningful for the latter analysis.

# Removing the NAs
df <- dataset[which(!is.na(dataset$Alter)),]

# Filtering the Dataset only for German speakers
df <- df[which(df$Muttersprache=="Deutsch"),]

# Filtering the columns
cols <- c('Name','Alter','Geschlecht','Geburtsort','HÃ¶chster Bildungsabschluss','Fach','Beruf','Muttersprache','Besten Aufnahme','Charaktereigenschaften','Aufnahme','Score','Sprache 1','Level 1','Sprache 2','Level 2','Sprache 3','Level 3','Sprache 4','Level 4')
df <- df[cols]

# Renaming the Columns
colsn <- c('Name','Age','Gender','Place of Birth','Highest Degree','Subject','Occupation','Mother tongue','Best Speaker','Trait','Speaker','Score','Language 1','Level 1','Language 2','Level 2','Language 3','Level 3','Language 4','Level 4')
names(df) <- colsn


# Converting to factors
df$Trait <- as.factor(df$Trait)
df$Gender <- as.factor(df$Gender)
df$`Mother tongue` <- as.factor(df$`Mother tongue`)
df$`Best Speaker` <- as.factor(df$`Best Speaker`)
df$`Highest Degree` <- factor(df$`Highest Degree`,ordered = TRUE, 
                                          levels = c("Unterer Schulabschluss", "Abitur oder gleichwertiger Abschluss","Bachelor","Postgraduierten-Abschluss","Master-Abschluss","Doktorat"))

# Counting the number of Languages
df['Languages'] <- 4 - is.na(df$`Language 1`) - is.na(df$`Language 2`) - is.na(df$`Language 3`) - is.na(df$`Language 4`)
df$Languages <- factor(df$Languages, ordered = TRUE, levels = c(1,2,3,4))

# Column with the german preference
df['German Preference?'] <- ifelse((df$`Best Speaker`=="Sprecher/in 1" | df$`Best Speaker`=="Sprecher/in 2"),"Yes","No")
df$German_Pref_01 <- as.numeric(as.factor(df$`German Preference?`))-1
df

ntraits <- unique(df_tr$Trait)
for (i in 1:length(ntraits)){
    df_t1 <- df_tr[which(df_tr$Trait == ntraits[i]),]
    res <- wilcox.test(Score ~ `German Preference?`, data=df_t1)
    print(paste(ifelse(res$p.value<0.05,"*",""),as.character(ntraits[i]),":", round(res$p.value,4)))
}
